eth","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Culcheth (Lancs)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry de Culcheth was born about 1175, in Culcheth, Lancashire, England as the son of Gilbert Sir Culcheth. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Baroness Cecilia de Lathom. He died in 1212, in Warrington, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 38."},"et":{"Abt 1175–1212":"umbes 1175–1212","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1184–1221":"1184–1221","1205–1275":"1205–1275","1225–1307":"1225–1307","1150–1212":"1150–1212","Abt 1175":"umbes 1175","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1212":"1212","1221":"1221","Abt 1205":"umbes 1205","1275":"1275","1175":"1175","1184":"1184","1150":"1150","1307":"1307","Culcheth, Lancashire, England":"Culcheth, Lancashire, England","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Culcheth Hall, Warrington, Lancashire, England":"Warrington, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warrington, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1175–1212":"noin 1175–1212","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1184–1221":"1184–1221","1205–1275":"1205–1275","1225–1307":"1225–1307","1150–1212":"1150–1212","Abt 1175":"noin 1175","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1212":"1212","1221":"1221","Abt 1205":"noin 1205","1275":"1275","1175":"1175","1184":"1184","1150":"1150",